On Space Exploration Day, the United States celebrates its accomplishments in space and commemorates the 50th anniversary of the first lunar landing. The Apollo 11 mission, where Neil Armstrong and Buzz Aldrin planted the American flag on the Moon, represents a remarkable era in American innovation and has inspired future generations to pursue careers in science and engineering. The United States pledges to launch a new era of exploration, with plans to send the next man and first woman to the Moon and eventually to Mars. This sustained exploration will bring advancements in science, technology, engineering, mathematics, and defense. The United States aims to reestablish its dominance and leadership in space for the future betterment of humankind.